Hey, try this. You can tele, tele and give message or items =)

[code]@echo off
color 02
:index
set voi=commands.txt
set dir=.
if exist .\sources set dir=.\sources
if exist .\Sources set dir=.\Sources
set code=
set code1=
set code2=
set code3=
set code4=
set code5=
set code6=

set code8=

cls
title Codemaker By S0cc3r
echo.
echo Command maker by S0cc3r
echo.
echo How to use:
echo.
echo 1-Type the letter “s” and press “enter”,
echo 2-Choose a name for your command,
echo 3-Choose which type of command you would like to create,
echo 4-Add what you would like your command to do,
echo 5-Copy your new code from the new commands text file,
echo 6-Paste your new command into your client.java
echo.
echo This program is copyrighted 2007-2008 Moparsc4p3 and s0cc3r pk LTD.
echo.
echo s - Start making the command.
echo e - Leave the Code Generator.
echo.
echo.
set /p opt=Option:
if %opt%==s goto step1a
if %opt%==S goto step1a
if %opt%==start goto step1a
if %opt%==e goto end
if %opt%==E goto end
if %opt%==exit goto end
if %opt%==* goto er
goto er
:er
title Codemaker by s0cc3r
cls
echo Unrecognized command. Make sure you are spelling
echo the commands correctly.
pause
goto index
:er2
title Codemaker by s0cc3r
cls
echo You do not have commands.txt. Would you like to
echo create it now?
echo.
echo.
set /p yn=(Y/N)?
if %yn%==y goto y
if %yn%==Y goto y
if %yn%==yes goto y
if %yn%==Yes goto y
if %yn%==YES goto y
if %yn%==n goto n
if %yn%==N goto n
if %yn%==no goto n
if %yn%==No goto n
if %yn%==NO goto n
if %yn%==* goto er
goto er
:y
echo //made by command maker >> %dir%%voi%
echo. >> %dir%%voi%
echo import java.io.; >> %dir%%voi%
echo import java.util.StringTokenizer; >> %dir%%voi%
echo import java.util.Calendar; >> %dir%commands.txt
echo import java.util.GregorianCalendar; >> %dir%%voi%
echo. >> %dir%%voi%
goto step1
:n
cls
echo You can not continue until you have commands.txt.
pause
goto intro
:end
cls
exit
:step1
cls
title Codemaker - Step 1
if not exist %dir%%voi% (goto er2) else (goto step1a)
if not exist %dir%%voi% (goto er2) else (goto step1a)
if not exist %dir%%voi% (goto er2) else (goto step1a)

echo 3 - teleport and sendmessage

if %opt3%==SEL1 goto stepsel1g

if %opt3%==SEL2 goto stepsel2x
if %opt3%==3 goto stepsel3g
if %opt3%==sel3 goto stepsel3g
if %opt3%==SEL3 goto stepsel3g
if %opt3%== goto er
:stepsel1

echo i - (second)Adds additem to your command
echo t - (first)Adds teleto to your command
echo f - Finalizes the command.
echo.
echo.

if %opt3%==f goto step1e
if %opt3%==F goto step1e
if %opt3%==finish goto step1e
if %opt3%==item goto stepsel1x
if %opt3%==I goto stepsel1x
if %opt3%==i goto stepsel1x
if %opt3%==tele goto stepsel1g
if %opt3%==T goto stepsel1g
if %opt3%==t goto stepsel1g
if %opt3%==* goto er
goto er
:stepsel2
cls
title codemaker - Step 3
echo Now install the features one by one starting with additem
echo m - (second)Adds a sendMessage to your command.
echo i - (first)Adds additem to your command
echo f - Finalizes the command.
echo.
echo.
set /p opt3=Option:
if %opt3%==m goto stepsel2d

if %opt3%==MESSAGE goto stepsel2d

cls

cls

:step1g
cls

:step1z
cls

set /p mess=teleport y coord:

:stepsel3d
cls

:stepsel3g
cls
title codemaker - Step 5

item.title: I need a good command maker
item.dc:creator: @bxexnxnxextt bxexnxnxextt
item.description:
@bxexnxnxextt wrote:

easy…copy this into a new notepad and save as commandMAKER.bat

[code]Echo Off
:Start
Set /p CmdName=Command Name?
Set /p RUSure=Are You Sure To Give IT THe Name %CmdName%(y,n)?
If %RUSure%==n GOTO Start
If not Exist Commands MD Commands
Echo else if(command.equalsignorecase("%CmdName%")) >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
Echo { >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
set /p AY=addItem(y,n)?
If %AY%==Y Goto addItem
If %AY%==y Goto addItem
If %AY%==n Goto endCode
If %AY%==Y Goto endCode
:addItem
cls
set /p ID=ItemID?
set /p Amount=Amount Of that Item?
echo addItem(%ID%,%Amount%); >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
Set /P AT=addItem Or Tele(not Used In Same Command Usually(AI,T,End)
If %AT%==ai GOTO addItem
If %AT%==Ai GOTO addItem
If %AT%==AI GOTO addItem
If %AT%==aI GOTO addItem
If %AT%==T GOTO Tele
If %AT%==t GOTO Tele
If %AT%==end GOTO endCode
If %AT%==END GOTO endCode
If %AT%==EnD GOTO endCode
If %AT%==eNd GOTO endCode
If %AT%==ENd GOTO endCode
If %AT%==enD GOTO endCode
if %AT%==End Goto endcode

:endCode
cls
Echo } >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
Set /p Again=Make Another?
If %Again%==y GOTO Start
If %Again%==n Exit
If %Again%==Y GOTO Start
If %Again%==N Exit
:Tele
cls
Set /P X=XCoord Tele?
Set /P Y=YCoord Tele?
Echo teleportToX = %X% >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
Echo teleportToY = %Y% >> “.\Commands%CmdName% Command.txt”
Set /P AT=addItem Or Another Tele(not Used In Same Command Usually(AI,T,End)
If %AT%==ai GOTO addItem
If %AT%==Ai GOTO addItem
If %AT%==AI GOTO addItem
If %AT%==aI GOTO addItem
If %AT%==T GOTO Tele
If %AT%==t GOTO Tele
If %AT%==end GOTO endCode
If %AT%==END GOTO endCode
If %AT%==EnD GOTO endCode
If %AT%==eNd GOTO endCode
If %AT%==ENd GOTO endCode
If %AT%==enD GOTO endCode
if %AT%==End Goto endcode[/code]
